subSubSection.paragraph:
Head
.

— Pale yellow to brown, impunctate. Antennae entirely black and only the first basal antennomeres usually contrasting pale yellow to brown (
Fig. 25
). Ratio length of second to third antennomere 0.75–0.83 (mean: 0.79); ratio length of third to fourth antennomere 0.40–0.50 (mean: 0.44; 
Fig. 26
).
